.TH "clean_buf" 9 "clean_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clean_buf \- clean the data from an LEB sitting in a buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clean_buf
.BI "(const struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "void **buf "  ","
.BI "int lnum "  ","
.BI "int *offs "  ","
.BI "int *len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to clean
.IP "lnum" 12
LEB number to clean
.IP "offs" 12
offset from which to clean
.IP "len" 12
length of buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function pads up to the next min_io_size boundary (if there is one) and
sets empty space to all 0xff. \fIbuf\fP, \fIoffs\fP and \fIlen\fP are updated to the next
\fIc->min_io_size\fP boundary.
